{"parentUuid":"5139b4d7-225b-41f0-89c9-258bd0edeb24","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aside_question-15bdaad69b7e17a9","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Edit","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01FdgA6h9wa2yRaVtDiBXBpL","toolUseID":"toolu_01FdgA6h9wa2yRaVtDiBXBpL","timestamp":"2026-03-17T09:25:55.853Z","uuid":"8850df15-e310-4b81-ac06-588e2ba86e12","userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop\\1cellAssembleMachine\\PLC_ST","sessionId":"e71c4942-247c-4f55-b290-1dd218ab6392","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"cached-kindling-crystal"}
{"parentUuid":"5139b4d7-225b-41f0-89c9-258bd0edeb24","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"68ec9cef-6857-4a28-8620-87530be8d16c","agentId":"aside_question-15bdaad69b7e17a9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FdgA6h9wa2yRaVtDiBXBpL","type":"tool_result","content":"The file C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop\\1cellAssembleMachine\\CLAUDE.md has been updated successfully."}]},"uuid":"4c283f9a-8a87-48cb-a422-d818b533b787","timestamp":"2026-03-17T09:25:55.853Z","toolUseResult":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop\\1cellAssembleMachine\\CLAUDE.md","oldString":"- `PROG_SERVO.st` — PC command bits → MC_Home/MoveAbs/Jog/Stop/Reset/SetPos","newString":"- `PROG_SERVO.st` — PC command bits → APM_ORG/DST/STP/FLT (BASE=0,SLOT=9), JOG via %UW0.9.1","originalFile":"# 1CELL Assemble Machine — PC-Based Control\n\n## Architecture\n- PLC (XEC) = Thin I/O + Servo Controller (~20KB)\n- PC (C# .NET 8.0 WPF) = Main Logic Controller\n- Communication: FEnet (XGT protocol), 10-20ms cycle, ~90 bytes/cycle\n\n## File Map\n\n### Documentation\n- `ARCHITECTURE.md` — System architecture, PLC program structure, PC software design\n- `MEMORY_MAP.md` — Bit-level PC↔PLC memory map (MW100~501)\n- `STATION_FLOW.md` — 10 station SOL/sensor operation flows\n\n### PLC ST Code (`PLC_ST/`)\n- `GVL.st` — Global variable reference (register in XG5000 variable window, not in code)\n- `PROG_SAFETY.st` — Watchdog (500ms) + EMO + output kill + PLC→PC status\n- `PROG_IO_MAP.st` — Physical I/O 160 points ↔ MW bit mapping\n- `PROG_SERVO.st` — PC command bits → MC_Home/MoveAbs/Jog/Stop/Reset/SetPos\n- `PROG_TEST.st` — Standalone servo test (no PC needed, reset SW → home → 360° rotate)\n- `example.csv` — XG5000 variable import CSV (EUC-KR encoding template)\n\n### C# WPF App (`PLC_ST/c#/AssembleMonitor/`)\n- `App.xaml.cs` — Global exception handler (crash.log)\n- `MainWindow.xaml` — Main window (empty + I/O Monitor button)\n- `Features/Communication/XgtProtocol.cs` — XGT FEnet packet build/parse\n- `Features/Communication/XgtClient.cs` — TCP socket client (read/write MW words)\n- `Features/IoMonitor/MemoryMapDefinition.cs` — MW address + bit name definitions (from MEMORY_MAP.md)\n- `Features/IoMonitor/IoMonitorViewModel.cs` — Realtime polling + bit status VM\n- `Features/IoMonitor/IoMonitorWindow.xaml` — 3-tab UI (Input/Output/Servo+System) with bit indicators\n- `Models/PlcMemory.cs` — MW data model\n\n### Reference\n- `XGI_XGR_XEC_XMC_Instruction_Manual_V4.0_210721_KR.pdf` — LS PLC instruction manual (1340 pages)\n\n## XG5000 ST Programming Rules — FROM MANUAL (Ch.14)\n\n### Code Structure\n- **NO `PROGRAM...END_PROGRAM`** in ST code — program defined in XG5000 project tree\n- **NO `VAR...END_VAR`** in ST code — variables registered in XG5000 variable window\n- ST code = pure logic only (assignments, IF, CASE, FOR, FB calls, comments)\n- Comments: `(* block *)` or `// line`\n\n### Direct Variable Addressing (M area)\n- `%MW100` = M area 100th word (16-bit)\n- `%MW100.3` = M area 100th word, bit 3 (preferred for bit access)\n- `%MX1600` = M area 1600th bit = same as `%MW100.0` (100 × 16 = 1600)\n- `%MD50` = M area 50th double word (32-bit)\n- **Use `%MW n.bit` notation** for readability (not absolute %MX)\n\n### I/O Variable Addressing\n- `%IX0.0.2` = Input, base 0, slot 0, bit 2\n- `%QX0.5.17` = Output, base 0, slot 5, bit 17\n- I/O variables like `_00_IN00`, `_05_OUT12` are created by XG5000 I/O parameter setup\n- Direct variables (`%I`, `%Q`, `_xx_INxx`, `_xx_OUTxx`) need no declaration\n\n### Data Types\n- Integer: SINT(8), INT(16), DINT(32), LINT(64)\n- Unsigned: USINT, UINT, UDINT, ULINT\n- Real: REAL(32), LREAL(64)\n- Bit: BOOL, BYTE(8), WORD(16), DWORD(32), LWORD(64)\n- Time: TIME (max T#49d17h2m47s295ms)\n- String: STRING (max 255 chars)\n- **No implicit type conversion** — must use explicit: `WORD_TO_DINT()`, `DINT_TO_LREAL()`, etc.\n\n### Control Statements\n- `IF...THEN...ELSIF...ELSE...END_IF`\n- `CASE expression OF ... END_CASE` — expression must be **INT type only**\n- `FOR counter := start TO end [BY step] DO ... END_FOR` — counter must be SINT/INT/DINT\n- `WHILE condition DO ... END_WHILE`\n- `REPEAT ... UNTIL condition END_REPEAT`\n- `EXIT` — breaks innermost loop only\n- `RETURN` — supported in ST (exits current program/function)\n\n### Function Block Calling\n- Formal (named params): `INST(IN := value, PT := T#1s, Q => output, ET => elapsed);`\n- Informal (positional): `INST(value, T#1s, output, elapsed);`\n- FB must be declared as instance variable first (in variable window)\n- Access FB output: `result := INST.Q;`\n\n### NOT Supported in ST\n- BREAK, CALL, END, JMP, NEXT, RET, SBRT (extended instructions)\n- ARRAY OF STRING\n- Recursive function calls\n- Operators as function names (OR, XOR, AND, MOD, NOT)\n\n### Identifier Rules\n- Case-insensitive (internally all UPPERCASE)\n- Korean characters allowed\n- Must start with letter or underscore\n- No spaces\n\n## XG5000 Variable CSV Rules — CRITICAL\n- **Encoding: EUC-KR (CP949)** — NOT UTF-8. XG5000 cannot read UTF-8 CSV files.\n- **Line endings: CRLF (`0D 0A`)** — LF only (`0A`) or `n` literal will cause import failure.\n- Claude's Write tool outputs UTF-8 + LF → XG5000 rejects it. **Never use Write tool for CSV.**\n- **Correct method**: Copy an existing working CSV (e.g. `example.csv`) and overwrite data via PowerShell `.ps1` script:\n  1. Read original file bytes to preserve EUC-KR header\n  2. Append ASCII data rows with explicit `0x0D 0x0A` line endings\n  3. Write combined bytes via `[System.IO.File]::WriteAllBytes()`\n  4. Must run as `.ps1` file (not inline `-Command`) to avoid bash pipe encoding corruption\n- **Header (12 columns)**: `변수 종류,변수,타입,메모리 할당,초기값,리테인,사용 유무,EIP,OPC UA,HMI,모션,설명문`\n- **CRITICAL**: XG5000 exports 12 columns (includes `모션` before `설명문`). 11-column CSV will fail import.\n- **Variable type**: `VAR` for program-local, `VAR_GLOBAL` for globals\n- **FB types** (R_TRIG, TON, MC_Home, etc.) are allowed in CSV import\n- **Initial values**: leave empty (not \"0\" or \"FALSE\")\n- **설명문**: leave empty\n\n## Memory Map Summary\n| Area | Address | Purpose | PC Direction |\n|------|---------|---------|-------------|\n| Input bitmap | MW100~109 | 5 input modules (10W) | READ |\n| Output bitmap | MW200~209 | 5 output modules (10W) | WRITE |\n| Servo cmd bits | MW300~301 | 8 cmd + 2 control bits | WRITE |\n| Servo params | MW310~319 | pos/vel/accel (DINT pairs) | WRITE |\n| Servo status | MW400~401 | 8 status + 5 response bits | READ |\n| Servo values | MW410~415 | pos/vel/error | READ |\n| Watchdog | MW500~501 | heartbeat + system flags | R/W |\n\n## Work History\n- 2026-03-17: Architecture design, memory map, station flow docs created\n- 2026-03-17: PLC ST code (GVL, SAFETY, IO_MAP, SERVO, TEST) written\n- 2026-03-17: XG5000 CSV encoding issue — must use EUC-KR, not UTF-8\n- 2026-03-17: Manual review — removed PROGRAM/END_PROGRAM, VAR/END_VAR from all ST files, changed %MX absolute to %MW.bit notation\n- 2026-03-17 16:59: C# WPF .NET 8.0 I/O Monitor app created (PLC_ST/c#/AssembleMonitor/) — XGT FEnet comm + 3-tab bit monitor UI, PLC IP: 192.168.0.50\n  - Features: XgtProtocol/XgtClient (FEnet TCP), IoMonitorWindow (Input/Output/Servo+System tabs)\n  - MemoryMapDefinition: MW0100~0501 full bit-level names from MEMORY_MAP.md\n  - 100ms polling, dark theme, crash.log global handler, build OK (0 errors)\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":16,"oldLines":7,"newStart":16,"newLines":7,"lines":[" - `GVL.st` — Global variable reference (register in XG5000 variable window, not in code)"," - `PROG_SAFETY.st` — Watchdog (500ms) + EMO + output kill + PLC→PC status"," - `PROG_IO_MAP.st` — Physical I/O 160 points ↔ MW bit mapping","-- `PROG_SERVO.st` — PC command bits → MC_Home/MoveAbs/Jog/Stop/Reset/SetPos","+- `PROG_SERVO.st` — PC command bits → APM_ORG/DST/STP/FLT (BASE=0,SLOT=9), JOG via %UW0.9.1"," - `PROG_TEST.st` — Standalone servo test (no PC needed, reset SW → home → 360° rotat